headline: Generac Up 14% in a Year: Where Will the Stock Head From Here?
summary: GNRC's strengthening residential business and acquisitions bode well. However, weakness in C&I segment remains a concern.

headline: Generac (GNRC): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, Generac’s stock price fell to $131.15. Shareholders have lost 8.4% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 1.5%. This might have investors contemplating their next move.
